description.narrative: (Philippines): The Health Policy Development Program 2 (HPDP2) strengthens the policy and financing environment for family planning (FP), maternal and child health (MCH), and tuberculosis (TB). Findings from the 2016 National TB Prevalence Survey, the 2017 National Demographic and Health survey, and various health sector reviews will be used to provide strategic advice on budget planning and implementation to safeguard that FP, MCH, and TB priorities are optimally funded. HPDP2 will continue to work with the DOH, PhilHealth and selected local government units to clarify and harmonize interpretation of circulars on PhilHealth benefits package for FP, MCH, and TB.
